==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Milksop
<hw>Milk"sop`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A piece of bread
sopped in milk; figuratively, an effeminate or weak-minded person.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To wed a <qex>milksop</qex> or a coward ape.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milk vetch</ent>⟦br⟧
